A MAN has appeared in court charged with attempted murder at a safari park.
Christopher Blaikie made a brief appearance in private at Stirling Sheriff Court on Wednesday charged with assault to severe injury, danger of life and attempted murder.
Blaikie is accused of stabbing a 21-year-old woman in the restaurant of Blair Drummond Safari Park on Monday.
The 24-year-old, from Livingston, made no plea or declaration and was remanded in custody.
He is expected to be fully committed for trial next week.
